com.percussion.cms.objectstore
Class PSDbComponent

java.lang.Object
  com.percussion.cms.objectstore.PSDbComponent
All Implemented Interfaces:
IPSCmsComponent, IPSDbComponent, Cloneable
Direct Known Subclasses:
PSCmsProperty, PSComponentSummary, PSContentType, PSContentTypeVariant, PSDbComponentCollection, PSDbComponentList, PSDbComponentSet, PSFolder, PSItemComponent, PSSlotType, PSSlotTypeContentTypeVariant, PSVariantSlotType, com.percussion.cms.objectstore.PSVersionableDbComponent
public abstract class PSDbComponent
extends Object
implements IPSDbComponent

Base class for all IPSDbComponents. Implements some of the methods that don't vary across all or many of the components that will be implemented in the CMS layer. Derived classes should override the abstract methods and clone.

PSDbComponent

protected PSDbComponent()

PSDbComponent

protected PSDbComponent(PSKey locator)
We guarantee that a component always has a non-null locator. This ctor guarantees that. The state of the constructed object is DBSTATE_NEW if the locator is not persisted, otherwise the state of the object is DBSTATE_UNMODIFIED if the locator is persisted.

Parameters:
locator - Never null. It does not need to be assigned or persisted. Each derived class must know the definition for its key parts. Once set, all keys passed to setLocator must match the definition of this key.

toXml

public Element toXml(Document doc)
See interface for description. The document generated by this class conforms to the following dtd (note that that the entries and values are logical and would need to be replaced with their correct runtime values to generate a valid dtd): 

    <!ELEMENT getNodeName() (getLocator().getNodeName()...)>
    <!ATTLIST getNodeName()
       state (DBSTATE_xxx) "DBSTATE_NEW"
       >

Note that since getNodeName() will return the derived classes node name, the derived class can use this method to generate the element and just add to it.

toDbXml

public void toDbXml(Document doc,
                    Element root,
                    com.percussion.cms.objectstore.IPSKeyGenerator keyGen,
                    PSKey parent)
             throws PSCmsException
See IPSDbComponent.toDbXml(Document,Element,IPSKeyGenerator,PSKey) for details. Creates an xml fragment properly formatted for the Rhythmyx server that will modify the database to make the db instance of this object consistent with this object. A resource designed to handle this document must be created by the implementor of the component. This document is for use w/ the default processor. This resource name must be specified in the processor's configuration data.

To allow multiple updates to be processed by the server, the document generated by this method will conform to one of the two following formats (where root is the passed in element):

If requiresActionNode() is true or parent is not null - 


    <!ELEMENT root (Action+)>
    <!ELEMENT Action (getNodeName())>
    <!ATTLIST Action
       dbAction #REQUIRED (INSERT | UPDATE | DELETE)
       >
    <!ELEMENT getNodeName() (as defined by toXml())>

    <!-- If the state is DBSTATE_NEW, the Action type is set to INSERT.
       If the state is DBSTATE_MODIFIED, the Action type is set to UPDATE.
       If the state is DBSTATE_MARKEDFORDELETE, the Action type is set to
       DELETE.
       -->

Otherwise - 


    <!ELEMENT root (getNodeName())>
    <!ATTLIST getNodeName()
       dbAction (INSERT | UPDATE | DELETE) "UPDATE"
       >
    <!ELEMENT getNodeName() (as defined by toXml())>

    <!-- If the state is DBSTATE_NEW, the Action type is set to INSERT.
       If the state is DBSTATE_MODIFIED, the Action type is set to UPDATE.
       If the state is DBSTATE_MARKEDFORDELETE, the Action type is set to
       DELETE.
       -->
In most cases, this method will generate the full element. It should only have to be overridden if the derived class contains any child IPSDbComponents. In that case, call this method first, then call this method for all child members, passing the same root.

Specified by:
toDbXml in interface IPSDbComponent
Parameters:
parent - The parent key of this object. It must be null if the key of the object does not contain parent key (as its foreign key); otherwise it must not be null.
doc - This document will be used to create the elements in the result xml fragment. Never null.
root - The generated element will be appended to this node. Never null. If the component doesn't need updating, it won't be appended.
keyGen - This object is used to create new keys when a component has a key that hasn't been assigned yet. Never null.
Throws:
PSCmsException - If any of the components of the specified type have unassigned keys.

toXml

protected Element toXml(Document doc,
                        boolean includeChildComps)
This method is called by the toDbXml(Document,Element,IPSKeyGenerator,PSKey) method. Derived classes without IPSDbComponents as children do not need to override this method. If the derived class has children, it must override this method and not include those in the generated Xml.

By default, this method just calls toXml(doc) since this method doesn't have any IPSDbComponent members.

Parameters:
doc - Used to generate the elements, never null.
includeChildComps - If true, equivalent to calling toXml(doc). If false, all IPSDbComponent members will not be serialized. They must be added individually with their own Action element at the root level.
Returns:
An element whose node name is the value returned by getNodeName(). Never null.

fromXml

public void fromXml(Element source)
             throws com.percussion.design.objectstore.PSUnknownNodeTypeException
See interface for description. The key is regenerated by taking the node name and using that to derive a class name. An instance of this class is created by passing the key's element to the ctor.

Each component must have a single argument ctor that takes an element and calls its fromXml. The derived class' fromXml must call this method (using super.fromXml) to restore the proper key and db state. Note that this would not be required when initially constructing from xml, but it is required if fromXml is called on an already instantiated object.

This method verifies that the name of the supplied element matches the name obtained with the getNodeName() method. If it doesn't, a PSUnknownNodeTypeException is thrown.

Specified by:
fromXml in interface IPSCmsComponent
Specified by:
fromXml in interface IPSDbComponent
Parameters:
source - The node to extract the data for this instance. Never null. See toXml for the required format of the supplied element.
Throws:
com.percussion.design.objectstore.PSUnknownNodeTypeException - If the element name is incorrect, if the key isn't correct (see PSKey.fromXml(Element)) or the state name is not valid.

setLocator

public void setLocator(PSKey locator)
Description copied from interface: IPSDbComponent
Sets the key that uniquely identifies this instance. Typically, this is only used by the system, as setting the wrong key could produce unexpected results. Setting a key may cause the state of this object to change to maintain consistency.

The following table shows all possible combinations between the assigned, persisted and state variables of the key and this component, indicating which are allowed and not. The 4 possibilities w/ assigned false and persisted true are left out because the key doesn't allow such a condition.

The various methods that affect these 3 properties maintain the contract as defined in the following table.

isAssigned isPersisted State Allowed
true or false false new yes
true or false false modified no
true or false false unmodified no
true or false false deleted yes
true true new no
true true modified yes
true true unmodified yes
true true deleted no

Specified by:
setLocator in interface IPSDbComponent
Parameters:
locator - An id appropriate for this object within the system. Never null. The definition of the supplied key must match the definition of the current key or an exception is thrown. A clone of the supplied key is stored locally, so subsequent changes to locator will not affect this object.

public void markForDeletion()
Description copied from interface: IPSDbComponent
If it is desired to remove a component from the database, call this method, then save the component. This is equivalent to calling the processor's delete method with this object's key.

If the object has not been persisted yet, this is a no-op.

equals

public boolean equals(Object obj)
Description copied from interface: IPSCmsComponent
Indicates whether some other object is "equal to" this one. All implementing classes must override this method as the default behavior is incorrect for deep clones. If the implementation does not follow the contract documented for this method in Object, then it must clearly state how it deviates from that contract. The following algorithm should be used:
  1. Call the base class (unless Object) and if true is returned, continue.
  2. Compare all members of current class.
  3. If all members are equal, return true.

Specified by:
equals in interface IPSCmsComponent
Specified by:

obj - the reference object with which to compare. May be null;
Returns:
true if this object is logically equivalent to the supplied obj; false otherwise. If null or not an instance of this class, false is returned.

getKeyPartValues

protected String[] getKeyPartValues(com.percussion.cms.objectstore.IPSKeyGenerator gen)
                             throws PSCmsException
This method allows derived classes to implement keys that are assigned from values in the component rather than from a generated id. The default implementation generates a single id using the supplied generator.

Any component property used as part of the key must be immutable, meaning that it must be set in the ctor and then never changed.

Parameters:
gen - Never null.
Returns:
A valid array with 0 or more entries. Each entry must be a non- null String (possibly empty). The returned values will be assigned to the key in the order they are returned. In other words, if keyDef[] contains the key definition, and values[] contains the return from this method, for each i, the value for key part keyDef[i] is assigned from values[i]. Any additional values in the key def are assigned from the foreign (parent) key.
Throws:
PSCmsException

getLookupName

protected String getLookupName()
The name of the 'key' in the next number table that contains the next id to be used for the component. By default, the name is generated from the component type by stripping the leading PS, lower-casing it and adding 'id'.

Returns:
Never null or empty.
